WITHIN the &#8220;01&#8221; sub-page. On the other hand, the doubles for the &#8220;contact&#8221; page are found in two different sub-pages (&#8220;11&#8221; and &#8220;03&#8221;). Here is the structure of the sub-pages of the site map:</p>\n<p>URL of sub-sitemap	Last modified (GMT)<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-misc.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-misc.xml</a>	2020-02-16 15:08<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2020-01.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2020-01.xml</a>	2020-02-08 14:09<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2019-11.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2019-11.xml</a>	2020-02-16 15:08<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2019-09.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2019-09.xml</a>	2020-02-16 09:24<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2018-03.xml\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://www.textile-du-maine.com/sitemap-pt-page-2018-03.xml</a>	2020-02-06 23:29</p>\n<p>3. Problems with Links on Plugin Settings page</p>\n<p>On the plugin settings page, all the links are broken underneath the titles, &#8220;About this plugin&#8221; and &#8220;Sitemap Resources.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Details of installation:<br />\n&#8211; WordPress 5.3.2 running Bridge theme.<br />\n&#8211; Plugin Version 4.1.0</p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Robert</p>\n						\n					\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"rreedmeister\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"\n					\n					\n					\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n\n					\n					\n					\n				\";s:7:\"attri